bug.short_desc: Compiz not clearing screen when drawing new frames
bug.cf_doc_type: If docs needed, set a value

long_desc.thetext:
Created attachment 1208791 screenshot of behaviour
Description of problem: all screen activity since enabling compiz is still on screen
Version-Release number of selected component (if applicable):0.8.12.3-3.fc25
How reproducible:consistently
Steps to Reproduce: 1.enable compiz 2.use the computer, screen fills with old frames 3.try reloading the window manager from fusion icon, more corruption
Actual results:as in steps
Expected results:normal rendering
Additional info:tested on AMD Athlon 5350 APU with R3 Graphics using Gallium and Also Intel i3-3110m HD 4000 GPU with Intel drivers. Same results so not driver specific.

Hi, known issue, see https://github.com/compiz-reloaded/compiz/issues/40 for more infos. You can use this workaround for the moment: Enable the wallpaper plugin and do a'killall caja', than the desktop icons are there and we have no redraw issue. You can also switch wallpapers in the plugin.
thanks, that works nicely for now
